    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As the old saying goes: hitting easy targets is like shooting fish in a barrel. You @UUID[Compendium.sf2e-anachronism.actions.Item.sLikawnrJJzHMYeC]{Aim} and then make a ranged Strike against a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.j91X7x0XSomq8d60]{Prone} or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.eIcWbB5o3pP6OIMe]{Immobilized} creature not benefiting from cover. Treat a success as a critical success. If you roll a critical success, the creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.AJh5ex99aV6VTggg]{Off-Guard} and @UUID[Compendium.sf2e-anachronism.conditions.Item.enA7BxAjBb7ns1iF]{Suppressed} until the beginning of your next turn.</p>",
